subSubSection.paragraph:
ETYMOLOGY. — Dedicated to the memory of Dr. S. Peigné (
1972- 2017
), who described numerous carnivorous mammals from the Paleogene and Neogene of Eurasia and Africa.

The genus 

Matthodon

is represented by two species: 

Matthodon
menui

from Chavot, Monthelon, Mancy, and Grauves (Ypresian, MP10; 
France
) and 

Matthodon
tritens

from Geiseltal- Untere Unterkohle (Lutetian, MP11; 
Germany
).

